European Stocks Climb as Deutsche Bank Beats Analysts’ Earnings Estimates

-- B y   J a s o n   C a r e y
-- 
2011-04-28T07:08:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/european-stocks-climb-as-deutsche-bank-beats-analysts-earnings-estimates.html
European stocks rose as companies
from Deutsche Bank AG to Novo Nordisk A/S posted earnings that
beat estimates and as the  Federal Reserve  pledged to keep
 interest rates  low for an “extended period.” U.S. futures and
Asian shares also gained.  Deutsche Bank rose 3.4 percent as Germany’s biggest bank
reported a 17 percent increase in first-quarter profit. Novo
Nordisk climbed 1.1 percent after saying first-quarter profit
rose 23 percent. Bayer AG gained 1.2 percent as Germany’s
largest drugmaker raised its forecast for sales and earnings
this year. Royal Dutch Shell Plc, Europe’s biggest oil company,
said profit rose in the first quarter as crude prices gained.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index added 0.4 percent to
283.11 at 8:05 a.m. in  London . The MSCI Asia Pacific Index
advanced for the first time this week, adding 1.2 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jason Carey at 
 jcarey3@bloomberg.net  